text: The North Washington Historic District in Brownsville, Tennessee is a historic district which was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2015. It includes 126 contributing buildings and 25 non-contributing ones, as well a contributing structure and three non-contributing sites. Includes 56 photos (see photo captions pages 38-39). It was listed on the National Register consistent with guidelines established in a 2014 study of historic resources in Brownsville. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Tennessee Category:Haywood County, Tennessee
title: North Washington Historic District
